author: Desperado
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2019
review_content: Ok so I opened these up and fell in love. I had originally wanted to order more saucony socks that look almost just like these .  But the Sauconys did not all have the vibrant colors on the little cuff.  Half were just black.These have really nice fabric-  they are really soft and nice and thick.  They seem very well made and I was totally thrilled with the quality and feel.I wear a size 8.5-9 shoe and these fit me perfectly.  However due to the shape I think they would be too big for someone with like a size 6.5 shoe or smaller.  I didn’t really have to stretch them to get them on.The big bummer came after I put them on and walked around. They were so comfy and soft and thick.... and this freakin tight little band is cutting into the front on my ankles with every step.  It feels like they inserted a thin 1/4” elastic band around the top edge of the ankle.It’s uncomfortable and annoying and too tight.  With every step I can feel it cutting across the individual tendons the house through my ankle and it’s intolerable.  For the record I am a tad over 5’2” and 135.So . Sadly I must return them. They came so close to being my everything

author: Linjab
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2020
review_content: My daughter and I love,love,love these socks. We ordered them in gray and black. See photo. My dog even loves them. Haha. Seriously,  I want more. I love the comfort. My daughter loves the look. We both like everything about them. The price is great ! They stay in place and not slip into your shoe. Thick and warm yet light enough for work outs. Some of the best quality I have seen.Update, We really love these socks. But don’t fall for the card placed inside that says they will give you money if you post a positive review. I really liked the socks but very much disapprove of offers that are fake promises.

author: Amanda Whiteaker
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2020
review_content: My husband purchased these as a stocking stuffer for me this year and I love them! I wear a size 10.5-11 in women's shoes and these fit great. Had I been looking at these myself, I probably wouldn't have gone with them because the description lists shoe sizes 6-10 with a sock size of 9-11, so I'm glad I wasn't the one shopping for these. I tend to get back-of-the-ankle blisters when my socks aren't adequate and so far these have done a great job preventing blisters. I highly recommend them!
title: Great Socks

author: Andrea
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2020
review_content: I just received my order a few days ago, washed and dried them (on low) and am wearing a pair again today, day 2. So far, they are very comfy with the extra compression support around the arch. I have very high arches, so this feels really good. The colors are very bright, which I should've prepared for, and the picture is very accurate. Neon assortment is really what it should say in the description. That's okay though, they're just socks and most of it will be covered by my shoe. I wish that was my biggest worry, what other people think about my socks!.... lol.  I own Bombas, and these are similar in compression and fit, but do sit a little higher on the ankle. The top of the sock rests at the top of my ankle bone, as expected. For the price, they are a solid group of socks and I would recommend them. 4 stars for now until I've washed them a few times to see how the stitching holds up. Will update rating once they've been broken in a bit.It's been enough time to give my follow up review now. Have washed them over a couple dozen times, and they've held up great! Same vibrant colors, very little pilling, and elastic is still great! I give these socks 5 stars surprisingly, since they are a brand I had never heard of prior to this purchase. Enjoy!
title: More comfy than I was expecting!

author: Keris
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 24, 2019
review_content: Great fit. Extra thick on the bottom for wear. Soft and very comfortable.  I like that there are different colors in the pack so you are not stuck with the same color every day.  I was worried about buying these online and not at the store, but these are like the ones from the stores but better. The fit is the same, great quality and these have the different colors and I never had to leave my house to get them.
title: Great quality

author: LC
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2019
review_content: I've worn these several times now. They are very comfortable.  I can tell there is extra padding underneath.  These are not "now show" socks as you can see them over your shoes, but not overly noticeable.  I've worn these to walk, run, and workout in and they stay in place with no rubbing of your heel area on your shoes.

author: Amazon Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 17, 2020
review_content: Got them today and wire a pair around the house.  The are comfortable and feel like they eont slide down in your shoe.  One draw back is that they made my ankle swell.  Above my ankle.  It doesn't feel tight at all.  Just snug.  If you retain water I would think twice.  I don't retain water and I had a line of demarcation when I took them off.  The rest will be when I wear them to work where I sit at a computer all day....  I like them....but....They feel well made otherwise.  Doesn't hurt me to try them out.  Beautiful colors for sure.  I'll wash a pair tomorrow night to see if they loosen up some.  They're also not to thick.  I hate thick socks.

author: Emily Peters
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 6, 2020
review_content: I had to wear these socks absolutely perfectly on my foot, or they’d hurt the front of my foot where it meets the ankle. I couldn’t get my running shoes off fast enough because it felt like they were cutting off circulation. D: These are the first socks that happened with and I’m perplexed about it. But once I made sure everything was “centered,” it wasn’t an issue, so I guess an annoyance, maybe?Also after two washes now, the socks have a lot of strings exposed on the inside.The only real positive is that these socks have a lip on the back to help with pulling up.

author: Natalie
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2019
review_content: If it is perfect I love these socks they are really soft and comfortable but they also have a nice little padding around the back end of your heel they’re really cute too I like the different colors and they fit right where I want them to right at the top of my ankle so they’re perfect I’m wearing shorts with sneakers
title: Fit is perfect

author: BSM
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2020
review_content: My initial impression was that they were thick and roomy in the toe. I wear a size 10 and sometimes find socks can be short in length. After less than 10 minutes wearing the socks around the house with no shoes I noticed I could see my toe in the left sock.  See photo.I suspect the high ratings are because they pay for them. Also in my photo is the card that was included with the socks offering to pay for reviews.
title: Poor quality. Pays for 5 star reviews.

author: Kindle Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2021
review_content: So I have issues with my feet, and therefore pretty much spend all my time in tennis shoes that were recommended by my podiatrist.  I also have to be extremely careful with my socks or it makes the situation worse.  I received these Eallco Women's Ankle Socks as a gift, and I absolutely love them!  First of all I was drawn in by the fun bright colors.  I am a sucker for neon so these socks fit the bill with a neon green, blue, pink, yellow and orange highlighting the black, but there's also an awesome pair of black and plum, that happens to go great with my new plum tennis shoes!  However, the look isn't enough to sell me on a product, but comfort and fit definitely is.  They are soft, fit great without moving around and causing issues with my feet, and they have a great cushion on the top of the heel to prevent chafing.  They don't slip down into my shoe, bunch at the toes or any of the other problems I have had with other socks that have resulted in a trip to the podiatrist.  I will definitely be purchasing more of these socks, and will definitely be recommending them to my family and friends.  A well designed, great product!  A+++++
title: I LOVE THESE SOCKS!

author: Terri Christiansen
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2021
review_content: I bought these awhile back.  I wanted to wait awhile before I reviewed them... BUY THESE SOCKS, lol.I have feet like a duck. They are flat,  extra wide,  yet I have a small heel. These feel so good on my feet. I've worn socks with that tight compression band around the middle of the foot, and I hated them.  It felt like they were strangling my feet.  These are not like that.  They have a band,  and I can feel it if I think about it,  but it's a really good feeling with these socks. I love wearing these socks. They have some kind of cushioning that doesn't bother me in sport shoes or make my shoes fit tight, but they feel so good on my hard wood and tile floors when I'm not wearing any shoes. Noticeably good and so soft.Looks wise, they are vivid in color.  Even after multiple washings. I was worried they would shrink after reading reviews so I dried them carefully, but they didn't.  After a couple weeks of drying them carefully,  I stopped being careful in the dryer. Now I throw them in with any load and dry them on whatever heat I need for the major load, and they don't shrink, at all.  I love these socks... and I'm picky about socks. I do wish I could choose the colors, some are a bit too vivid for an older person like me lol
title: You Do Want These Socks

author: Mindy Copeland
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2020
review_content: I recently got a pair of name brand cushioned socks for Christmas. They made a huge difference in comfort and stability when I worked out.  When I looked them up to order another pair or two I fell over when I saw the price. I happened to find these on amazon and figured I’d give them a try. I am SUPER impressed! I see absolutely no difference in quality and performance from the brand that cost a bunch more just for one pair than this brand which came in a package of 6. They held up beautifully in the washer/dryer as well. If you want to step up your workout game (pun intended) then grab a pack of these socks!
title: Socks matter!

author: Master
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2020
review_content: Your browser does not support HTML5 video.                       These socks feel so so nice!!!I will admit way better than some big brands like Nikes, Under Armor, or even Calvin Klein!I usually get picky with socks since I tend to be one to run around a lot, be everywhere on my feet & even do heavy duty stuff every so often like Yard Work or Deep Cleaning the entire living space.So my other socks would usually tear since they were also somewhat more thin in material...always disappointed that “Woman’s Socks” have to be so thin in material!!!I’d wear men socks but most of the time, due to the difference in sizes, would fit me so BIG! Both men & Gals, haha.Very great, I know they’ll last me a long time.

author: Erica
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 22, 2021
review_content: I LOVED these socks, ...until I wore them for long days. The stitching/ zigzag pattern around the center of your foot (arch area) is basically squished into your skin as it is in the inside of the sock. It's extremely painful and irritating for me. If you wear any type of snug shoes this happens (with my rain boots, work boots, and tennis shoes. Around the house (in socks only, no shoes) this doesn't happen. The sizing is correct and I've never had this problem with other socks. I hate it because they are very well made and soft otherwise. Would not recommend and won't buy these again :( The search for the perfect sock continues.

author: Lynn
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 17, 2021
review_content: I play pickleball, and I have constantly been frustrated by how so many of my socks that get pulled down in my shoes.  My husband bought me these for Christmas, and let me say that I LOVE these socks!  They look good, they have a snugger, tighter band around your arches which give great support, they do not get pulled into your shoes, and they stay completely in place.  They wash well and have held up beautifully after washing one pair or another daily.  I am about to order more of these!  I truly love them!  I have no idea how my husband chose this brand but I am so glad he did.  This will be my go to sock from now on!
title: Love these socks

author: Christopher J. Carlson
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 8, 2020
review_content: Update:  customer service did contact me and apologize for the poor fit. They informed me they would be adjusting the sizing so that in a few weeks they would be more true to size.  I appreciated them reaching out and do recommend these socks ultimately. I wear an 8.5 and they are WAY too big.
title: Huge

author: Toddler Mom
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 10, 2021
review_content: I am nearly *40* years old.I have ALWAYS HATED SOCKS.As a result of hating to wear socks, I have always hated sneakers. (well at least for my adult life)Thanks to the amazing people I have met in RTI I have been MOVING a lot more and I broke down and bought myself a pair of sneakers.  I then had to get a second pair because wearing sneakers 2 days in a row when they didn't dry out from sweating the first day is ... EW!I splurged and treated myself to GOOD socks.  Not like just fancy schmancy socks, but socks recommended by members who are runners in the RTI family.Uhm ... HOLY CRAP!  Guys.  Good socks with good shoes makes a difference!  I VOLUNTARILY WORE MY SNEAKERS ALL DAY LONG AND DIDN'T SWAP FOR MY SANDALS AT FIRST CHANCE I GOT!So ... yeah, I am almost 40 bleeping years old and just learning that good socks make a difference.

author: Verified Reader
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 4, 2020
review_content: I am one of those kinds of people that when I find a good thing, I keep going back until they stop making them. I hope they make these socks forever. author: Amazon Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2021
review_content: I purchased these because of all the great reviews.  These are comfy socks, they are just too thick for me.  I was looking for thinner, footie-like socks for running. I will wear them around the house but that's about it, and I didn't really need socks to wear around the house but didn't bother to return them.  I would say these would be good to wear with boots in cold weather, but the part at the back of the heel makes wearing with boots uncomfortable.  However, I would certainly purchase a mid-calf or taller style for cold weather because these would definitely keep your feet warm in boots.

author: Karen T.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 8, 2020
review_content: I'm giving these socks one-star because they're already starting to fall apart after just three weeks. They're very soft and comfortable and give good support. author: Jamie

I have no complaints and will absolutely be purchasing more!

author: kirsten w.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 13, 2021

Ive washed them 3 times already and they still look brand new and haven't lost their shape and for the price you really can't beat it. I bought 2 packs the black and white and will be buying more!

author: eze2525

author: Kasey
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 14, 2021
review_content: I'll preface this by stating - I am a B*mbas fan through and through. I noticed the arch support stitching right away, so I decided to take the plunge. I'm happy I did! While these are not as thick all around as B*mbas ankle socks, they are cushioned around the entire bottom of the foot and the stitching is functional, just like B*mbas, but for a fraction of the price. Don't get me wrong, I will still opt for B*mbas for other sock types, but I might not look back when it comes to ankle socks.

author: daisyross
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2021
review_content: These socks are great for all kinds of exercise, or just for everyday activities. They're super comfortable and look cute too. I particularly like the tighter band around the middle, and the added cushion on the toe and heel for all kinds of workouts. They also have the tab at the back so they don't scrunch down into your sneakers. I have both the gray and black sets, and the quality is consistent. Some reviewers have mentioned that they're big. I have found that after a couple of washes they shrink to just the right size. I wear a 7.5 and they're perfect for me. I wear a pair of these almost every day no matter what I'm doing. Highly recommended!

author: Cynthia
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 29, 2021
review_content: Okay. I didn't want to like these for a reason after I got them, but I figured I'd give them a try. They felt tight around the center part of the foot - unlike Bombas. I also haven't had an instance of sweaty feet, cold or hot feet, or the seam by the pinky toe digging into my toe.UPDATE 06/19/21My feet seem to swell a lot. I never had this problem before I started to wear these socks. My inner ankles get so swollen and are so painful up my inner leg from ankle to knee.

author: DC
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 26, 2021
review_content: I wear a women's 9.5-10 shoe and hate wearing socks. But I also live where it's winter and sometimes we gotta do stuff we don't wanna do. So, socks! author: Traveln_Circus

author: trixiebelle

author: kh808

author: V. Johnson
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2021
review_content: Luxurious, high-quality socks. I love them. author: L D Parker
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2021
review_content: They are nice and thick. Especially along the bottom for a little extra cushion where you need it. I just got the yesterday and they came neatly in a plastic pouch. author: JLC
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2021
review_content: For exercise, I walk on average 25-30 miles every week, 1.5-2.5 hours (6-10 mi) at a time, always wearing these Eallco socks.  The socks are comfortable, feel slightly padded, and don't slip down because of the tab at the heel.  I was not completely convinced they made a difference until my 9.5 mi walk this morning.  I  didn't have a pair of these handy so I just used one of my other socks and that was a huge mistake.  The last 1.5 mi or so were painful.  I could feel the thinner threading of these "other" socks rubbing on the balls of my feet and by the time I managed to finally get to my car, I was on the verge of having a blister.  3-hours later and my feet still hurt.  With the Eallco socks, my feet would get tired from the walking but I have never experienced the issue that I had today from using my other socks.  I ordered another set so I won't run out if I don't finish my laundry in time.
title: absolutely make a difference

author: SPurr
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2021
review_content: I own a few pairs of Bombas, which I like (I also like their mission, though I’m pretty sure the cost for all their donated socks is passed along to the customer). The seam at the toes is comfortable and the tab on the heel keeps them in place while running.  I will definitely buy these again, including some extra pairs to donate to homeless shelters on my own!

author: anne
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2021
review_content: These socks are perfect (I know- odd to say about socks). They are soft, comfortable, not tight but don’t slide down. And lets mention the thickness- not so thick that my feet become swampy (gross- but most of you know what I mean) but not so thin that my feet reek by the end of the day- that hard to find middle thickness. I’ve worn & washed these socks a few times and the still look/feel just like new. I am actually back on here buying another package when I thought I’d leave a review- So as odd as it sounds- these socks are perfect.
title: If you need socks- get these!!

author: Indy
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2021
review_content: I don't know about you but I'm always looking for the perfect pair of socks. While this pairs aren't for myself as they are for my teen daughter, I truly like them.Pros:Plush socksFun colorsAnkle styleThey look and feel comfyCons:Just received them so I'm not sure how long they'll last???!Elasticity seems on the soft side so I wouldn't recommend for any pressure points.Overall, great product for the price. Exactly what my daughter wanted.

author: Jennifer Haynes Anderson
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2021
review_content: The socks are well padded and the tabs at the heel and front of the ankle keep them from sliding down. They make my feet hot, so I only wear them for walks outside.  The ribbing around the arch of the foot isn't any tighter than the rest of the sock, which is a negative for me,  I need extra support.  Overall, they are good socks, but not as good as I expected from the description.

author: Melforliv
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 8, 2021
review_content: Years ago I purchased a ton of Feetures brand socks for my wife. She absolutely loved the way they felt. However, the last time I went to purchase more for her, they were unavailable. My wife loves them and they, in her opinion, are a superior product to her previously favorite socks.
title: A great replacement

author: JesaLore
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2020
review_content: These socks are just what I was looking for. I tend to prefer a darker colored ones because it's hard to keep white socks looking clean even if they are but oftentimes the dark ones are no fun so the bright colors here are very welcome. The material is nice and thick on the bottom but very breathable on top and has a nice amount of stretch around the arch. The tabs in the back keep my shoes from eating them which is always a plus in slushy winter weather. They held up fine in the washer and machine dryer.

author: K. Anderson
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 6, 2021
review_content: I love these socks so much that I have purchased several pairs for myself as well as family members. They are thick and soft as well as tight-fighting (compression) around the arches. I’ve suffered from plantar fasciitis for years and these really help. I’m just disappointed that the cost keeps going up. I originally purchased them for $13, the second time it was $15 and now they are almost $17. I still think that is a fair price for a six-pack of socks, but they have gone up in price in just a matter of weeks.
title: I’m obsessed with these socks!

author: Juniormint
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2021
review_content: These socks actually fit! I wear a size 9.5 shoe.  These socks fit snugly. They are form-fitted around all parts of your foot, even the arch. This is important because many socks tend to slip during workouts. These stay up. I have worn them during step class, while lifting weights and while kickboxing. No issues. If your foot is larger than a size 10, these socks might be too tight for you. If your feet are smaller than a 10, these are nice socks. Their thickness is better than average. I have worn all 6 and washed them. They are holding up and keeping shape so far. I would buy them again, perhaps in more muted colors or just plain black. They are comfortable and can be worn for workouts or everyday leisure.
title: These socks actually fit!

author: ChloKins
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 15, 2021
review_content: Way way better than I was expecting. These 100% comparable with the big name-brand running socks (Bo...).  I got 6 pairs for less than the price of one of the brand name. Would probably be a little big for a size 7 or 8. The heel tab in the back is perfect to keep the socks from sliding down in your shoe. Love them!

author: Barbara
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2021
review_content: I'm not much of a sock wearer but, on cooler nights, these are great too keep feet warm in bed. They stay put in sneakers, too. They're just too big now. If you're foot is smaller than an 8...these will be too long for you.

author: Michelle Kippelen
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2020

author: Amazon Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 21, 2021
review_content: I've run in these socks multiple times (mostly cement running and up to 9 miles at a time) and love them. Definitely recommended for other athletes or just wearing around the house because they keep your feet nice and warm!

date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2021
review_content: These are really nice but if you have had foot surgery and have pins and screws in your foot, these might be too tight.
